qas.question: Which model suggests that matter is 5% of the universe?
What type of matter does the model consider it to be?
Which model suggests that matter is 0.5% of the universe?
What type of matter does the model believe it to not be?
The standard model believes none of the universe is composed of what?

context: According to the dominant cosmological model, the <a0_0><b2_0>Lambda-CDM model<b2_0/><a0_0/>, less than 5% of the universe's energy density is made up of the "matter" described by the Standard Model of Particle Physics, and the majority of the universe is composed of <a1_0><b3_0><b4_0>dark matter<b3_0/><a1_0/> and dark energy<b4_0/> - with little agreement amongst scientists about what these are made of.
